When parameterizing JComboBox in the Source tab and switching to the Design tab a warning is thrown that prevents the Design tab from displaying anything. 
Warning: 
```
Invalid source. No constructor binding.
new JComboBox<>(array) is not valid source for component creation, it references not existing constructor.
```

Work around is to take out the parameters in the constructor which then throws an IDE warning.

Example code:
```
// Noncompliant code that breaks the Design tab
String[] array = {"asdf", "jkl"};
JComboBox<String> comboBox = new JComboBox<>(array);

// Compliant code that throws an IDE warning
String[] array = {"asdf", "jkl"};
JComboBox<String> comboBox = new JComboBox(array);
```

